@startuml HospitalPrescriptionWorkflow
title Hospital Management System — Prescription → Stock → Oversight Workflow\n(Process View, role-based access enforced at every hop)

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 4
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEFEC8

actor "Doctor\n(doctor_cardio)" as D
actor "Nurse\n(nurse_cardio)" as N
actor "Pharmacist\n(pharmacist1)" as P
actor "Manager\n(manager1)" as M

participant "Controller\n(views.py)" as C
participant "Permissions\n(permissions.py)" as Perm
database "ORM + DB\n(Django models)" as DB

== Phase 1 — Doctor prescribes ==

D -> C  : POST /records/<id>/prescribe/\n(drug=Atorvastatin, dosage=20 mg)
C -> Perm : can_write_prescription(doctor, record)
Perm --> C : True\n(record.appointment.doctor.user == doctor)
C -> DB  : INSERT Prescription
DB --> C : OK (rx_id)
C --> D  : 302 redirect → /records/<id>/prescribe/\n(POST-redirect-GET; doctor can add more drugs)

note over D, Perm
  WRITE permission lives in the matrix (§3.5);
  enforcement is one function call, not scattered if-checks.
end note

== Phase 2 — Nurse reads (department-scoped) ==

N -> C  : GET /nurse/prescriptions/
C -> Perm : route guard: role == NURSE
Perm --> C : OK; nurse.department == Cardiology
C -> DB  : SELECT Prescription\nWHERE medical_record.appointment.doctor.department == Cardiology
DB --> C : rows including newly-added Atorvastatin
C --> N  : render read-only list

note over N
  Nurse sees the medication but
  CANNOT modify it — and cannot
  see Pediatrics or Neurology rows.
  Department scope is enforced in
  the ORM filter (defense in depth).
end note

== Phase 3 — Pharmacist adjusts stock after dispensing ==

P -> C  : POST /pharmacy/stock/<id>/adjust/\n(quantity ← quantity − 10)
C -> Perm : can_write_drug_stock(pharmacist)
Perm --> C : True (role == PHARMACIST)
C -> DB  : UPDATE DrugStock\nWHERE drug=Atorvastatin AND department=Cardiology
DB --> C : updated row (quantity = 8, reorder_level = 10)
C --> P  : 302 redirect → /pharmacy/stock/

note right of DB
  is_low = quantity <= reorder_level
  Atorvastatin @ Cardiology: 8 ≤ 10 → **LOW**
  No event bus needed — the dashboard
  query computes "low" on read.
end note

== Phase 4 — Manager sees low-stock alert ==

M -> C  : GET /management/
C -> Perm : can_view_management_dashboard(manager)
Perm --> C : True (role == MANAGEMENT)
C -> DB  : SELECT DrugStock\nWHERE quantity <= F('reorder_level')
DB --> C : rows including Atorvastatin @ Cardiology
C -> DB  : aggregate Equipment by status
C -> DB  : aggregate Appointment count by department
C --> M  : render management dashboard\n(low stock + equipment + appointment volume)

note over M
  Manager sees aggregate operational state.
  No PHI — patient names are NEVER joined
  into the dashboard query (see SAD §3.5).
end note

== Negative paths (would terminate at the Permissions check) ==

note across
  • Patient hits any of the URLs above → permissions returns False → controller returns 403
  • Nurse hits /pharmacy/stock/<id>/adjust/ → can_write_drug_stock returns False → 403
  • Pharmacist hits /management/ → can_view_management_dashboard returns False → 403
  Every denial is a uniform 403 via permissions.deny() — no info leakage.
end note

@enduml
